{
  "text": "Let (U, x = (x, y)) be a local chart of Σ, where (x, y) are isothermal parameters for the first fundamental form, and consider the complex parameter z = x + iy, which is conformal, this is I = 2λ|dz| 2 . It is well known that ∆x = 2HN , where ∆ is the Laplace-Beltrami operator (see [CITATION_1] ). This allows us to conclude that Σ is minimal in R 3 if, and only if, the coordinate functions are harmonic. We define",
